entries.femaleVariant: Hey, hey, everyone, welcome to Infoflash. Say, did y'all lose power yesterday too?
Yeah, when the lights went out there I was cooking dinner... Well, if we're gettin' specific, I was nukin' a half-eaten burrito I found wedged in my couch cushions.
Yeah, yeah, I know I shouldn't have... After all, I heard microwaves zap out all the nutrients. But hey, it kills the cockroaches too, so ya know... You win some, you lose some.
Anyway, what was I... Right, the power outage. Apparently, some plant out in Santo short circ'd. Heard the EMPs were knockin' AVs outta the sky.
The NCPD says the blackout led to a hundred and twenty mill in damages all in all. The real tragedy though? I can't stomach a cold burrito...
120 million eddies?! Hot damn. And just to get your hands on one dude.
Oh Ruth, it coulda been worse... so, so much worse.
The NCPD claims losses were minimal considering the scale of the incident. I dunno... depends on perspective, man. I had to stomach an ice-cold burrito...
